description: Tranmere Rovers and Barrow share the spoils in a 1-1 draw in League Two
title: Tranmere Rovers and Barrow share the spoils in a 1-1 draw
title_page: Tranmere Rovers and Barrow share the spoils in a 1-1 draw - BBC Sport
maintext:
Tranmere lost both league games against Barrow last season; they’ve never lost three successive games to the Bluebirds in the Football League before.
After beating Tranmere 2-1 on the opening day of last season, Barrow are looking to win on successive visits there in the Football League for the first time since March 1967.
Tranmere are unbeaten in their final Football League game of the calendar year on each of the last seven occasions (W4 D3), winning each of their last three such games.
Barrow haven’t won their final Football League game of a calendar year since 1967 (4-1 against Oldham), with the Bluebirds drawing three of their four such games since returning to the Football League in 2020 (L1).
